<body lang="en-US" link="#0000ff" dir="ltr">
  {{> header unmudlLogo = unmudlLogo}}
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in"><br />
    <br />

  </p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in"> {{date}}</p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">Dear {{recipient.fullname}},</p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">
    You’ve just accepted your gift from {{sender.fullname}}: {{course.title}}, offered by {{college.title}}. Now, for
    the next steps!
  </p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">Monitor your email address:</p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">
    Either before or after the college admits you, it may need to reach out to you by email or phone in order get
    additional information to register you in their systems and/or to get any required documents from you. Once you are
    accepted for admission, the college may also send you an email you with information on how to access your course –
    whether it’s a room you need to show up to, an online course whose login information you ‘ll need, or a special
    announcement regarding the course itself. Please keep checking your email until the course is live and you are
    safely on your way.
  </p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">
    Check your “My Enrollments” section:
  </p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">
    <a name="_GoBack"></a>
    For many (but not all) online courses, many will appear in your “My Enrollments” section with a “Launch Course”
    button next to it. This button will become active on the first day of the course.
  </p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in"><br />
    <br />
  </p>
  <p align="center" style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">
    <b>Refunds</b>
  </p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">
    <u>Courses with “Cancel Enrollment” Button</u>
  </p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">
    Up until the college admits you, a “Cancel Enrollment’ will appear next to your course within the “My Enrollments”
    section of your account . If you click this button , the pending charge on the gift-giver’s credit card will be
    reversed, and that card will receive a 100% refund. Once the college admits you, the gift giver’s credit card will
    be charged, and the button will change to “Request Refund.”
  </p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">
    <br />
    <u>Courses with “Request Refund” Button</u>
  </p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">
    The “Request Refund” button allows you to request a refund from the college after you have been admitted to the
    course and a credit card has been charged. Clicking this button will open a request to the college. These refunds
    are subject to a 3% + 30¢ processing fee.
  </p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in"><br />
    <br />
  </p>
  <p align="center" style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">
    <b>Feedback to Unmudl:</b>
  </p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">
    As one of our earliest customers, any feedback you wish to provide would be gratefully received. Feel free to reach
    out to us at <font color="#0000ff"><u><a href="mailto:{{supportMail}}">{{supportMail}}</a></u></font>
  </p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">
    Thank you, and we’re really excited to have you aboard! --The Unmudl Team at Social Tech
  </p>
